author: Sarah D.
title: ‘Nice spin’: Notice anything missing from this CNN headline about WH fence jumper?
text:
— Chris Velcro (@Velcro108) March 27, 2017 
The White House seems to have a fence-jumping problem. Here’s how CNN covered three-time jumper Marci Anderson Wahl: A woman is arrested three times as she tries to see President Trump https://t.co/gPQvpDwHlw pic.twitter.com/JZ7UpA2eqj 
— CNN Politics (@CNNPolitics) March 27, 2017 
Nice headline, CNN. Why does Trump refer to the media as the enemy? Do they cover his White House different than the last? Confused. pic.twitter.com/TYzVOQpt8s 
— Vincent Casimir (@vncnt_csmr) March 27, 2017 
It really is a mystery. . @CNNPolitics ummmm nice headline there #FakeNews CNN 
— Virgil Edwards (@The_Virg_) March 27, 2017 She jumped the fence. What the fuck is this headline? https://t.co/m57oTCxOzO 
— Cassandra Fairbanks (@CassandraRules) March 27, 2017 Trending 
It’s crap, is what it is. (I fucking loathe Trump, but seriously?) 
— Vincent Casimir (@vncnt_csmr) March 27, 2017 "Youths are arrested as they attempt to see the inside of an unoccupied residence at 3am." 
— Vincent Casimir (@vncnt_csmr) March 27, 2017 "Group of strangers are arrested as they try to see museum during closed hours." 
— Vincent Casimir (@vncnt_csmr) March 27, 2017 
Sheesh.
